4.1.beta2	12-19-2000 
	Fix the RESTRICT statement - (first attempt)
	
4.1.0 
	Setup the Hazard package with autoconf. This simplifies the 
	installation process on all platforms, and hopefully makes it more
	platform independent.

4.3.0 2012/02/26
	Correct the likelihood function when using weighting. Update all
	macros to latest versions from the CCF production set.

4.4.3 2026-04-23
	Acceptance-harness-proven baseline. Binary behaviour is identical
	to v4.4.2; this release carries a parity certification, not new
	features.

	* Acceptance harness: tests/validate_corpus.sh runs all 15 hazard
	  + 8 hazpred inputs through the modern binary, auto-selects the
	  reference corpus from host toolchain family (Darwin/arm64 →
	  v4.4.2-macos-arm64, Linux/Windows → v4.3.0), normalises version
	  strings and timestamps, byte-diffs against the selected
	  reference.
	* Reference corpus: ships captured v4.3.0 CCF ground truth plus a
	  v4.4.2-macos-arm64 self-consistency capture. Cross-platform FP
	  divergence between gcc (Linux + Windows/MinGW) and Apple clang
	  on arm64 is documented in ROOT-CAUSE-ANALYSIS.md and
	  tests/corpus/FINDINGS.md — confirmed not a code-history
	  regression.
	* hazpred SIGSEGV fix: null FILE* deref at src/hazpred/opnfils.c
	  on missing INHAZ now produces a clean exit=16 with
	  "cannot open INHAZ file" instead of crashing.
	* TMPDIR buffer overflow fix: 80-byte stack buffer in opnfils.c
	  replaced with PATH_MAX + snprintf.
	* Capture kit: `make capture-kit` produces a self-contained
	  tarball of the operator-facing capture scripts, SAS macros, and
	  instructions for regenerating the reference corpus on a CCF
	  legacy host. See tests/CAPTURE_INSTRUCTIONS.md.
